review_blob: 16oz can from Instagram trade. Pours a milky yellow color with a small foamy white head. Aroma of B.O., sweet fruit, strawberries, white grapes, pineapple, lactose sugar, and light piney/evergreen. Taste mince the nose with a little more grassy/graininess, and citrus bitterness. Delicious
beer_name: Tired Hands / Omnipollo Milkshake IPA - Lychee

review_blob: 12oz bottle from Xroads. Pours a super hazy straw color with a small foamy white head. Aroma of rotted peaches, light pineapple, floral hops, and Brady malts. Taste of bad pineapple juice, lemons, grass, and sweet bready malts. Sweetness is a little too cloying.

16oz can from www.davedoesdudes.com! Pours a hazy dark orange color, with lots of floaties, and a finger of foamy white head. Aroma of caramel malt, grapefruit, rotted lemon and oranges, pine, and some floral hop notes. Taste mimics the nose, with a bready yeasty finish.

16oz can thanks to Dave Mac! Pours a hazy orange color with a finger of foamy white head. Aroma herbal and citrusy hops, citrus zest, grass, hints of pine, and sweet bready malts. Taste mince the nose. More citrus zest and pine in the flavor then in the aroma. Another nice dank rendition of 0dub!

16oz can from trade on Instagram. Pours a thick oily black color with a small creamy dark tan head. Aroma of rich espresso, black malts, creamy milk chocolate, vanilla, and caramel candies. Taste of black malts, charred coffee beans, rich black espresso, dark chocolate, vanilla beans, sweet caramel, and earth. Thick, rich, and complex. So solid!
beer_name: Tired Hands Only Void - Reanimator Ethiopia

review_blob: 16oz can from Instagram trade. Pours a hazy straw color with a finger of frothy white head. Lots of floaters. Aroma of dank citrus, ripe pineapple, cat piss, and bready malts. Taste is also full of dank citrus and cat piss, some pine sap, grapefruit zest, and bready malts. Love my citra hops! This beer is great!
ACBF 2016. Poured a hazy honey yellow color with a small foamy off white head. Aroma and flavors of toasted grain, honey, smoked malts, plastic, and yeast.

ACBF 2016. Firkin. Poured a dark brown/almost black color with a small creamy dark tan head. Aroma of chocolate, palo Santo wood, dark malts, and vanilla. Taste of chocolate, dark malts, palo santo wood, and caramel and vanilla in the finish. Mouthfeel a little thin. Solid though
beer_name: Spellbound Palo Santo Porter - Vanilla Bean
